
[1]infinity

   INFIN'ITY, n. [L. infinitas.]

   1. Unlimited extent of time, space or quantity; boundlessness. We apply
   infinity to God and his perfections; we speak of the infinity of his
   existence, his knowledge, his power, his goodness and holiness.

   2. Immensity; indefinite extent.

   3. Endless or indefinite number; a hyperbolical use of the word; as an
   infinity of beauties.
